div.div:
If we cache all rows, then we should just sync by sequence order.
If we limit our cache to a size (limit=1000), then we should retrieve the first 1,000 rows, truncate the table to the first 1000 rows and then set our after to be the latest the server sends us.
The server needs to return to us what the next "after" should be. Or else we just make it the max value in our 1000 rows.
what happens when the user scrolls to the 1,001 row?
Even if we sent the largest seq we have out of our first 1000 rows, the next one should be the 1,001 row. So rather than a hard limit, we could maintain a cursor into the latest change and when the user fetches the "next" and maintain the max of the new window. So it will be possible that old record 1,001 is actually newer than any record in 1-1000. But if we use the latest message id in our 1-1000 range, we will still pick up the change to record 1,001
